          "explanation": "The complement of a sum equals the product of complements."
        },
        {
          "q": "What is a minterm?",
          "marks": 1,
          "answer": "A product term where all variables appear exactly once in complemented or uncomplemented form.",
          "steps": [
            { "step": 1, "action": "Definition", "expression": "Product term with all variables", "law": "Boolean Algebra" }
          ],
          "explanation": "For n variables, there are 2^n minterms."
        },
        {
          "q": "What is the output of X · X'?",
          "marks": 1,
          "answer": "0",
          "steps": [
            { "step": 1, "action": "Apply Complement Law", "expression": "X · X' = 0", "law": "Complement Law" }
          ],
          "explanation": "A variable ANDed with its complement always gives 0."
        },
        {
          "q": "Write the dual of A + (B · C).",
          "marks": 1,
          "answer": "A · (B + C)",
          "steps": [
